        </p>
      </li>
      <li xml:id="exer_sec72-powerset">
        <p>
          Let <m>U</m> be a nonempty set and let
          <m>\mathcal{P} ( U )</m> be the power set of <m>U</m>.
          That is, <m>\mathcal{P} \left( U \right)</m> is the set of all subsets of <m>U</m>.
